HEADWORD: Pyrula
<hw>Pyr"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>pyrus</ets> a pear.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of large
marine gastropods having a pear-shaped shell. It includes the
fig-shells. See <xex>Illust.</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

